<TITLE> HC orders govt to explain decision on Bar Council membership </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 9 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court ordered the government Monday to explain why senior Supreme Court lawyer ABM Nurul Islam cannot be a member of the Bangladesh Bar Council after law minister Shafiq Ahmed resigned the post. The bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossaina and Quamrul Islam Siddiqui made the order on a writ petition filed by Islam on Mar 5. The chairman and the secretary of the council and the attorney general have been asked to reply in two weeks. The petitioner said Shafiq Ahmed was made vice-chairman of the council after he had been elected a member. But he did not resign his membership though he quit his vice chairmanship. He also said he became eighth in the voting that elected seven members. Islam added he could be a member if the law minister resigned his membership. Attorney general Mahbubey Alam said since Shafiq relinquished his vice-chairman post, he was no longer a member, because one has to be a member first to become an office-bearer. b
